  <section id="about" class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>About Cancer</h2>
      <p>Cancer refers to a collection of related diseases where cells in a part of the body grow uncontrollably. It can affect almost any part of the body, forming tumors and sometimes spreading to other areas.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="types" class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Types of Cancer</h2>
      <p>Here are some common types of cancer:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Breast Cancer</strong> – Affects breast tissue.</li>
        <li><strong>Lung Cancer</strong> – Starts in the lungs.</li>
        <li><strong>Prostate Cancer</strong> – Affects the prostate gland in men.</li>
        <li><strong>Skin Cancer</strong> – Develops in skin cells.</li>
        <li><strong>Colorectal Cancer</strong> – Starts in the colon or rectum.</li>
        <li><strong>Blood Cancer</strong> – Includes leukemia, lymphoma, and myeloma.</li>
        <li><strong>Brain Cancer</strong> – Originates in brain tissues.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="symptoms" class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Symptoms of Cancer</h2>
      <p>Symptoms vary depending on the type of cancer, but common ones include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Unexplained weight loss</li>
        <li>Chronic fatigue</li>
        <li>Changes in skin appearance</li>
        <li>Persistent cough or difficulty breathing</li>
        <li>Unusual lumps or swelling</li>
        <li>Frequent infections</li>
        <li>Changes in bowel or bladder habits</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="precautions" class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Precautions to Prevent Cancer</h2>
      <p>Adopt these habits to reduce your cancer risk:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Avoid tobacco products</li>
        <li>Maintain a healthy weight through diet and exercise</li>
        <li>Limit alcohol consumption</li>
        <li>Protect your skin from UV rays</li>
        <li>Get vaccinated against certain viruses (e.g., HPV, Hepatitis B)</li>
        <li>Regular cancer screenings</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

